  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan) / gas 7</p><p>Tip: This is just to warm your flatbreads later (alternatively, just pop them in the toaster)</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in cold water (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p><p>Slice the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!) to a large bowl with<strong> </strong>a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>marinade</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>pork steaks </strong>to the bowl and gently mix it all together then set aside to marinate</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed the <strong>cucumber</strong> (slice in half lengthways then scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon)</p><p>Dice <strong>half</strong> the <strong>cucumber</strong> and grate the remainder</p><p>Dice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p><p>Deseed the <strong>green pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced tomato </strong>and<strong> diced cucumber</strong> to a bowl</p><p>Drizzle with<strong> olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>Greek salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1069.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high</p><p>Thread the<strong> marinated pork</strong> and <strong>chopped green pepper</strong> evenly onto the <strong>soaked skewers</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>skewers</strong> to a baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess!)</p><p>Put the tray under the grill for 12-14 min, turning once halfway through, or until everything's cooked through (no pink meat!) and slightly charred – this is your <strong>pork souvlaki</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
